Malaysia is affected by seasonal storms, which occasionally result in heavy flooding. The timing of these storms depends on location in the country. Check local weather.
Between 18-20 December, there was unusually heavy rain in Malaysia. This has resulted in flash flooding particularly affecting Kuala Lumpur, Pahang, and Selangor, and also Kelantan, Melaka, Negeri Sembilan, Perak, and Terengganu. In some affected areas it has been necessary to switch off electricity and water supplies. Roads may be closed at short notice. If the rainy weather continues, more areas may become affected. Please consult local authorities or local media for updates.
Earthquakes are known in Malaysia, but rare.
